Developers frequently get confused and try to call chrome.* APIs from content 
scripts.

We would like to add some stub APIs that would tell developers that these 
APIs are not available from content scripts and refer them to the docs on how 
to use background pages.

An easy way to do this is like:

chrome.__defineGetter__(&quot;tabs&quot;, function() {
  throw new Error(&quot;chrome.tabs is not supported in content scripts&quot;);
});

From Cole:

The tips that can cycle through showing Mac keyboard shortcuts should follow Apple's normal 
documentation style by:

1. Using hyphen not plus between the modifier(s) and key.

2. If there is a modifier besides command (⌘) it should be listed *after* command.  (We seem to 
have a mix of some before and some after).

so:

  &quot;Shift+⌘+F&quot; should be &quot;⌘-Shift-F&quot;
  &quot;Shift+⌘+B&quot; should be &quot;⌘-Shift-B&quot;
  &quot;⌘+Shift+T&quot;  should be &quot;⌘-Shift-T&quot;
